propsDoc.Name: absolute
propsDoc.Description: Applies position: absolute to the component.

propsDoc.Name: active-class
propsDoc.Description: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active. You can find more information about the active-class prop on the vue-router documentation.

propsDoc.Name: absolute
propsDoc.Description: Setting append prop always appends the relative path to the current path. You can find more information about the append prop on the vue-router documentation.

propsDoc.Name: block
propsDoc.Description: Expands the button to 100% of available space.

propsDoc.Name: bottom
propsDoc.Description: Aligns the component towards the bottom.

propsDoc.Name: color
propsDoc.Description: Applies specified color to the control - it can be the name of material color (for example success or purple) or css color (#033 or rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5)). You can find list of built in classes on the colors page.

propsDoc.Name: dark
propsDoc.Description: Applies the dark theme variant to the component. You can find more information on the Material Design documentation for dark themes.

propsDoc.Name: depressed
propsDoc.Description: Removes the button box shadow.

propsDoc.Name: disabled
propsDoc.Description: Removes the ability to click or target the component.

propsDoc.Name: elevation
propsDoc.Description: Designates an elevation applied to the component between 0 and 24. You can find more information on the elevation page.

propsDoc.Name: exact
propsDoc.Description: Exactly match the link. Without this, '/' will match every route. You can find more information about the exact prop on the vue-router documentation.

propsDoc.Name: exact-active-class
propsDoc.Description: Configure the active CSS class applied when the link is active with exact match. You can find more information about the exact-active-class prop on the vue-router documentation.

propsDoc.Name: fab
propsDoc.Description: Designates the button as a floating-action-button - round.

propsDoc.Name: fixed
propsDoc.Description: Applies position: fixed to the component.

propsDoc.Name: height
propsDoc.Description: Sets the height for the component.

propsDoc.Name: href
propsDoc.Description: Designates the component as anchor and applies the href attribute.

propsDoc.Name: icon
propsDoc.Description: Designates the button as icon - round and flat

propsDoc.Name: input-value
propsDoc.Description: Controls the button's active state.

propsDoc.Name: large
propsDoc.Description: Makes the component large.

propsDoc.Name: left
propsDoc.Description: Aligns the component towards the left. This should be used with the absolute or fixed props.

propsDoc.Name: light
propsDoc.Description: Applies the light theme variant to the component.

propsDoc.Name: link
propsDoc.Description: Designates that the component is a link. This is automatic when using the href or to prop.

propsDoc.Name: loading
propsDoc.Description: 로딩 아이콘 애니메이션을 추가

propsDoc.Name: max-height
propsDoc.Description: Sets the maximum height for the component.

propsDoc.Name: max-width
propsDoc.Description: Sets the maximum width for the component.

propsDoc.Name: min-height
propsDoc.Description: Sets the minimum height for the component.

propsDoc.Name: min-width
propsDoc.Description: Sets the minimum width for the component.

propsDoc.Name: outlined
propsDoc.Description: Makes the background transparent and applies a thin border.

propsDoc.Name: replace
propsDoc.Description: Setting replace prop will call router.replace() instead of router.push() when clicked, so the navigation will not leave a history record. You can find more information about the replace prop on the vue-router documentation.

propsDoc.Name: retain-focus-on-click
propsDoc.Description: Don't blur on click.

propsDoc.Name: right
propsDoc.Description: Aligns the component towards the right. This should be used with the absolute or fixed props.

propsDoc.Name: ripple
propsDoc.Description: Applies the v-ripple directive.

propsDoc.Name: rounded
propsDoc.Description: Applies a large border radius on the button.

propsDoc.Name: small
propsDoc.Description: Makes the component small.

propsDoc.Name: tag
propsDoc.Description: Specify a custom tag used on the root element.

propsDoc.Name: target
propsDoc.Description: Designates the target attribute. This should only be applied when using the href prop.

propsDoc.Name: text
propsDoc.Description: Makes the background transparent.

propsDoc.Name: tile
propsDoc.Description: Removes the component's border-radius.

propsDoc.Name: top
propsDoc.Description: Aligns the content towards the top.

propsDoc.Name: type
propsDoc.Description: Set the button's type attribute

propsDoc.Name: value
propsDoc.Description: The value used when the component is selected in a group. If not provided, the index will be used.

propsDoc.Name: width
propsDoc.Description: Sets the width for the component.

propsDoc.Name: x-large
propsDoc.Description: Makes the component extra large.

propsDoc.Name: x-small
propsDoc.Description: Makes the component extra small.
